ἡ γραφὴ λέγει.] The same phrase is used Rom. iv. 3, V. 17, x. 11, Gal. iv. 30, 1 Tim. V. 18, cf. above ii. 23, and &Vestcott Heb. p. 474 on modes of citation. For the personification see Lightfoot on Gal. iii. 8. To show the incompatibility of being at the same time friends with the world and friends of God, the writer refers to the mode of speaking common in the O.T. where jealousy is ascribed to God.
